  "text": "As a model system, we use four highly invasive ants, among a pool of several invasive ant species that have been shown to have potentially overlapping suitable areas and are likely to encounter each other in the future [CITATION_1] ). They were also selected because they have been previously shown to interact aggressively and to form a linear dominance hierarchy in interference competition [CITATION_2] ): Wasmannia auropunctata > Lasius neglectus > Linepithema humile > Pheidole megacephala. This made them ideal candidates to test the existence of asymmetries in different types of competitive abilities and a potential trade-off among them.",
